value.0: Kenny is a young lad who likes to help his uncle in the shop. Ever since his father's death in the Sharran attack which demonlished the forge and the old church, he has clung to his uncle and learned from his mercantile lessons.

One of the cousins in the extensive Grogan family, this young woman is a skilled tailor. She's happy to share her skills with others.

((Job System Trainer))

Decades ago, a craftsman by the name of Jasper went to gather flotsam from the shoreline. Jasper crafted furniture, knick-knacks, and other souvenirs from the material. One day he returned carrying a young elf in his arms, skin dark like the bark of the black cherry tree. Jasper never spoke of how he came into possession of the "teenage" elf, but he raised him as his own and named him Karyon. When Karyon came of age and showed an aptitude for magic, Jasper bid him to go and learn of his people in Winya Ravana. Years later, when Jasper was upon his deathbed, Karyon returned from Winya and, in a decision that surprised many in the village, chose to stay and carry on something of Jasper's trade in the predominantly human fishing village.
A black robe.  Fine for walking about town, and being seen at the Nomad.  Not very practical for battle however.

The Moonpier premier tanner, Frederick, handles almost all leatherworking done in town. He's often too busy to talk and leaves his apprentice to handle adventurers looking for work. His wife tends the shop.

Value.value: Speak to my apprentice if you need something. I'm quite busy.

value.0: This fellow is surrounded by leather, and looks as if he might have something to say.

Value.value: Ahoy! We're on the lookout for gator skin. We'll give you some coin if you bring some back. Don't matter what kind or where you get it, but I've heard there's some in the swamps, and some big'uns over in Greengarden! Just bring it back here if yer inclined.
What a beaut! Thank ya for the help! Here's yer gold, as promised.

value.0: Benita is the gentle, soft-spoken wife of the local tanner. She tends to the shop which sells her husband's crafted materials, and offers her own selection of tailored clothing, as well.

Kindra is Kenny's older sister, the only daughter of Zeek Grogan, who died in the Sharran attack of 1388 DR. The two siblings are the only survivors of their immediate family, and have been living with their uncle ever since. With Zeek's Emporium opened in her father's honor, she handles the potion sales for the Selunite clergy.

Miss Forgison is a Waukeenar from Baldur's Gate who took a fancy to Moonpier during a trip to the isle. She stayed and decided to help people learn mercantile skills.

((Job System Trainer))

Zander is the eldest Grogan son. When his younger brother Zeek died, he took his niece and nephew in and cared for them over the years. When he heard about the plans for the tradehouse, he decided they would work together as a family to honor Zeek's memory. Now, they run Zeek's Emporium, which sells a wide variety of magical items crafted by various Moonpier residents. 10% of all profits go straight to the church and further renovation projects.
A member of the Moonpier Militia. They seem intent on their duties of protecting the town, wearing equipment that appears to be of high grade, glowing softly with an internal light.

A tracker's dream come true - Spectral Vision. This helm is so highly prized by assassins and other sophisticates because there's no known recipe to replicate the polished crystalline lenses that amplifies the wearer's sight tenfold.
This is a settlement guard insignia for the guard templates.

Frostbite Bolts are lethal projectiles crafted from enchanted ice, honed to subdue the fury of undead flames. Upon impact, they unleash a numbing cold that saps the life force of their targets, leaving them weakened and vulnerable. These icy bolts are the bane of burning undead and even the most powerful of infernal sorcerers - like the legendary Burning Lich said to reside in a crypt along the west coast of Amia.

A Frostblessed weapon, crafted in Moonpier, stands as a divine symbol of righteousness and resilience, forged to confront the darkness that plagues the land. Infused with the chill of winter, each swing of this weapon brings forth a biting cold. Its enchanted head, adorned with celestial runes, carries the essence of positive energy. The weapon is surprisingly lightweight, allowing its wielder to maneuver with grace and agility in battle. Notably, it proves particularly effective against the burning undead which plague the west coast of Amia.

Moonshriek blades, crafted in Moonpier, are formidable weapons born under the watchful gaze of the moon. They possess a unique property, resonating with the sonic frequencies of night. When wielded against shapechangers, they unleash a devastating sonic blast, disrupting their shifting forms and leaving them vulnerable to subsequent attacks. Their keen edges ensure that wounds inflicted are severe and debilitating. As weapons of the night, Moonshriek blades are both elegant and deadly, particularly useful in the endless battle against Malar's children.

The Guardian's Vigil Shield is a bastion of defense, crafted for those who stand as protectors and guardians on the battlefield. Emblazoned with celestial symbols, this shield exudes an aura of indomitable fortitude. Its imposing presence inspires allies and deters adversaries, marking its bearer as a formidable force to be reckoned with.

Beyond its defensive capabilities, this shield also harbors a subtle enchantment, granting its wielder steady regeneration. This boon ensures that even amidst the chaos of combat, the shield's bearer remains ready to endure the trials of battle. As a symbol of protection and resolve, the Guardian's Vigil Shield stands as a symbol of strength for those who defend the weak.

This is a cloak of exceptional quality and craftsmanship, designed to enhance both agility and defense for its wearer. Woven from the finest materials and adorned with subtle yet elegant embellishments, it exudes an air of sophistication and grace. This cloak serves as a versatile asset on the battlefield. It boasts a subtle enchantment that enhances the wearer's overall resilience, offering added protection against a variety of threats. Whether facing physical harm, magical attacks, or other dangers, the cloak's mystical aura serves to bolster the wearer's defenses and ensure their survival. As a symbol of grace, agility, and resilience, it is a coveted garment for adventurers.

Wearing it close to the heart, one can feel a subtle but reassuring presence, as if bolstered by an unseen presence.

As a symbol of strength, vitality, and resilience, this trinket is a cherished possession for adventurers.

This emerald is a marvel of arcane craftsmanship, a precious gemstone infused with potent magical energies.
